-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest
-- 
-- Tue Dec 09, 2014 10:58PM EST
-- None



Dec 10 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* The board of BT Group Plc <BT.L> met on Tuesday to discuss the possible acquisition of British mobile operators O2 or EE, and agreed to continue talks with both sides, a person familiar with the situation said. [ID:nL6N0TT2T8]  * Citigroup Inc <C.N> is in the final stages of talks with Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corp (SMBC) on the sale of its Japanese retail banking operations for about 40 billion yen ($334 million), sources with knowledge of the matter said. [ID:nL3N0TT3YB]  * Baby boomer-focused catalog retailer Orchard Brands Sales Agency LLC is putting itself up for sale in a process that could fetch more than $500 million, people familiar with the situation said on Tuesday. The company has hired Goldman Sachs Group Inc <GS.N> to assist with the sale, the people said. [ID:nL1N0TS1VI]  * U.S. aviation support company AAR Corp <AIR.N> has begun the sale of cargo handler Telair in a deal that could value the German business at up to 800 million euros ($988 million), three sources familiar with the matter said on Tuesday. [ID:nL6N0TT3JK]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]